               <msContents>
                  <summary>Psalter, ዳዊት፡</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1"><locus from="1r" to="135v"/><title type="complete" ref="LIT2701Dawit"/>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gə‘əz</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="Codex">
                     <supportDesc>
                        <support>
                           <watermark/>
                        </support>
                        <extent>
                           <measure unit="leaf"/>
                           <dimensions type="outer" unit="mm">
                              <height/>
                              <width/>
                              <depth/>
                           </dimensions>
                        </extent>
                     </supportDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                  <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                  <seg type="rubrication">
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢግዚአብሔር፡</foreign>
                  The word God is not rubricated in the first three works
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡</foreign>
                  <desc>The word Mary is rubricated in the final two works; there is no columetric layout of text</desc>
                  </seg>
                  </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                  <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d01">
                  Decorative designs:
                  <locus target="#69r #103v"/> (haräg); lined of alternating red and black dots are used as section dividers throughout;
                  <locus target="#68v"/> (multiple full stops);
                  <locus target="#103r #114v #121r #135v"/> (multiple full stops and lines of alternating red and black dots)
                  </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="a01">
                    <desc type="Asmat">
                    <locus target="#ir(ecto)"/>", upper: Asmat prayer against wild animals. Beneath the prayer is a pentrial
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a02">
                    <desc type="Asmat">
                    <locus target="#ir(ecto)"/>", lower: Asmat prayer for child birth
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a03">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#iir #iiv"/>: excerpt from the Hymn to Tewodǝros, incomplete at the end
                    Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሰላም፡ ለከ፡ ቴዎድሮስ፡ ስርጉዕ፡ ለቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ሞገሳ፡</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a04">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#135v #136r #136v"/>: <title type="complete" ref="LIT3032RepCh312"/>
                    Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሰላም፡ ለከ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ ዘልዳ፡ መስተፅዕነ፡ ፈረስ፡ ፀዓዳ፡</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e01">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#iv(erso)"/>": text has been erased and is illegible
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e02">
                    <desc>
                    There is text in the top margin throughout the Psalter providing instructions for when and how to recite the Psalms detailing the situation, anointing, and number of times of reading. Cf.                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e03">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#53r"/>: the mid-point of the Psalms is marked with a line of alternating red and black dots
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e04">
                    <desc>
                    Identified in the insurance hand list as Psalter 16
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e05">
                    <desc>
                    Navigation system:
                    red yarn is sewn into the fore edge of <locus target="#1 #114 #128"/>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e06">
                    <desc>
                    Psalm 118 does not contain the spiritual meanings of the Hebrew letters
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e07">
                    <desc>
                    Scribal intervention: words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#29r #32r"/>);
                    and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#8v #16r #20v #31v #49r"/>, etc.);
                    text has been removed (<locus target="#17v #124r"/>)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
